{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:41:37.759424+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, the personal access token doesn't have write access to this repository (403 error). I cannot push changes directly. Here's a summary of the issue and the exact changes I prepared to implement:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #5 Summary\n\n**Title:** Add endpoint allowlist documentation\n\n**Problem:** Document which local demo endpoints are intentionally in scope for the ZAP baseline workflow.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:** Changes to `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` and `docs/in_scope_endpoints.md`.\n\n---\n\n## Prepared Changes\n\n### 1. `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml`\n\nThe existing file (SHA `1ed3a796`) was minimal with no context. The updated version adds descriptive comments explaining purpose and a cross-reference to the docs:\n\n```yaml\n# Endpoint Allowlist for ZAP Baseline Scanning\n# Only the local demo application is intentionally in scope.\n# See docs/in_scope_endpoints.md for full documentation.\n\nin_scope:\n  - http://127.0.0.1:8080/    # Local demo app (IP)\n  - http://localhost:8080/     # Local demo app (hostname)\n```\n\n### 2. `docs/in_scope_endpoints.md`\n\nThe existing file (SHA `c9968c45`) was a one-liner. The updated version provides full documentation:\n\n```markdown\n# In-Scope Endpoints\n\nOnly local demo endpoints listed in `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` are in scope.\n\n## Why these endpoints are in scope\n\nThis repository is designed for local ZAP baseline testing against a simple demo application.\nThe demo app runs on `127.0.0.1:8080` via Docker Compose and exposes a minimal HTTP service.\nThe ZAP baseline scan is intentionally scoped to this local-only service to avoid scanning\nproduction or external targets.\n\n## Currently in-scope endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `http://127.0.0.1:8080/` | Local demo app via IP address |\n| `http://localhost:8080/` | Local demo app via hostname |